<BaseLayout
	title="About — Eduardo Macetas"
	description="Agentic Engineer with 5+ years of experience building web, mobile and AI-powered applications. Based in Lima, Perú."
>
	<main class="wrapper about">
		<header class="about-header">
			<h1>About me</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">
				QA Automation Engineer with 7+ years of experience in web,
				mobile and API testing. Based in Arequipa, Perú.
			</p>
		</header>

		<div class="about-grid">
			<section class="section">
				<h2>Background</h2>
				<div class="prose">
					<p>
						I specialize in building quality processes and
						automation frameworks from the ground up. Throughout my
						career I've been the first QA hire at multiple companies
						— defining testing strategies, creating test case
						libraries, and implementing automation that scales with
						the product.
					</p>
					<p>
						At GuideCX I built the entire QA process from scratch,
						reaching 85% test coverage with Cypress and later
						leading the migration to Playwright. At The Church of
						Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints I modernized a
						large-scale automation framework, migrating from
						Selenium + Appium + Cucumber to WebdriverIO. Most
						recently at Subscribe I built manual and automated
						testing processes covering 7+ client configurations and
						validated REST APIs with Postman.
					</p>
					<p>
						I work across the full testing spectrum — manual,
						automation, API, mobile (Android & iOS) and performance
						— using AI tools like Claude and GitHub Copilot to write
						scripts faster and generate test cases from
						requirements.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section">
				<h2>Experience</h2>
				<div class="prose">
